steps.step: Stir in 4 cups broth, sweet potatoes, lentils and bay leaf. Increase heat to high and bring to a boil; reduce heat to medium, partially cover, and simmer for 25 minutes. (If lentils seem dry, add up to 1 cup stock, as needed.) Stir in chard and salt and pepper, and continue cooking until lentils are tender and chard is cooked, about 30 to 45 minutes total.
Just before serving, stir in cilantro, lime zest and juice. Spoon into a large, shallow serving dish.
Garnish with almonds if desired and scallions.See more: Beans, Indian, Photo, Potatoes, Vegan, Vegetarian
